#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.28"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.28:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.28:0.2"
msgid "3. Sabbavagga"
msgstr "3. All"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 28. Ādittasutta → ādittapariyāyasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.28:0.3"
msgid "28. Ādittasutta"
msgstr "28. Burning"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.28:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā gayāyaṃ viharati gayāsīse saddhiṃ bhikkhusahassena."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Gayā on Gayā Head together with a "
"thousand mendicants."

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.3"
msgid "“sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, ādittaṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, all is burning."

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.4"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ ādittaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the all that is burning?"

#. VAR: Cakkhu → cakkhuṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.28:1.5"
msgid ""
"Cakkhu, bhikkhave, ādittaṃ, rūpā ādittā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ ādittaṃ, "
"cakkhusamphasso āditto. Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ "
"sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi ādittaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The eye is burning. Sights are burning. Eye consciousness is burning. Eye "
"contact is burning. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises "
"conditioned by eye contact is also burning."

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.6"
msgid "Kena ādittaṃ?"
msgstr "Burning with what?"

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.7"
msgid ""
"‘Rāgagginā, dosagginā, mohagginā ādittaṃ, jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi "
"paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi ādittan’ti vadāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Burning with the fires of greed, hate, and delusion. Burning with rebirth, "
"old age, and death, with sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress."

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.8"
msgid ""
"jivhā ādittā, rasā ādittā, jivhāviññāṇaṃ ādittaṃ, jivhāsamphasso āditto. "
"Yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi ādittaṃ."
msgstr "The ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.9"
msgid "Kena ādittaṃ?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.10"
msgid ""
"‘Rāgagginā, dosagginā, mohagginā ādittaṃ, jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi "
"paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi ādittan’ti vadāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.11"
msgid ""
"mano āditto, dhammā ādittā, manoviññāṇaṃ ādittaṃ, manosamphasso āditto. "
"Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi ādittaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The mind is burning. Thoughts are burning. Mind consciousness is burning. "
"Mind contact is burning. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that "
"arises conditioned by mind contact is also burning."

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.12"
msgid "Kena ādittaṃ?"
msgstr "Burning with what?"

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.13"
msgid ""
"‘Rāgagginā, dosagginā, mohagginā ādittaṃ, jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi "
"paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi ādittan’ti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"Burning with the fires of greed, hate, and delusion. Burning with rebirth, "
"old age, and death, with sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I "
"say."

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.14"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi "
"nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati, "
"yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, "
"sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with "
"the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye "
"contact. "

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.15"
msgid ""
"yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā "
"adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … "
"painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind "
"contact."

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.16"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn35.28:1.17"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.28:2.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn35.28:2.2"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanduṃ."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn35.28:2.3"
msgid ""
"Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne tassa bhikkhusahassassa anupādāya "
"āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti."
msgstr ""
"And while this discourse was being spoken, the minds of the thousand "
"mendicants were freed from defilements by not grasping."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.28:2.4"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
